The paper discusses the design of chatbots from a human-computer interaction perspective, which is the primary focus of the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper also discusses natural language processing and conversational agents, which are relevant to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also touches on the social and ethical implications of chatbot design, which could fall under the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
